{"schema_version":"1","crate":"utilada_unit","version":"2.8.2","id":"5249519251fd2bd9","name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets","qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets","kind":"ada_package","location":{"file":"../../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/utilada_2.8.2_30b22a59/4ad568c8d185b13a4b0f496912d263f14b692e0709f1ccf771a1531595b64c8f/src/base/beans/util-beans-objects-datasets.ads","line":55,"column":9},"code":"package Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets","documentation":{"description":"== Datasets ==\nThe `Datasets` package implements the `Dataset` list bean which\ndefines a set of objects organized in rows and columns.  The `Dataset`\nimplements the `List_Bean` interface and allows to iterate over its rows.\nEach row defines a `Bean` instance and allows to access each column value.\nEach column is associated with a unique name.  The row `Bean` allows to\nget or set the column by using the column name.\n\n   with Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets;\n   ...\n      Set : Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets.Dataset_Access\n          := new Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets.Dataset;\n\nAfter creation of the dataset instance, the first step is to define\nthe columns that composed the list.  This is done by using the `Add_Column`\nprocedure:\n\n   Set.Add_Column (\"name\");\n   Set.Add_Column (\"email\");\n   Set.Add_Column (\"age\");\n\nTo populate the dataset, the package only provide the `Append` procedure\nwhich adds a new row and calls a procedure whose job is to fill the columns\nof the new row.  The procedure gets the row as an array of `Object`:\n\n   procedure Fill (Row : in out Util.Beans.Objects.Object_Array) is\n   begin\n      Row (Row'First) := To_Object (String '(\"Yoda\"));\n      Row (Row'First + 1) := To_Object (String '(\"Yoda@Dagobah\"));\n      Row (Row'First + 2) := To_Object (Integer (900));\n   end Fill;\n\n   Set.Append (Fill'Access);\n\nThe dataset instance is converted to an `Object` by using the `To_Object`\nfunction.  Note that the default behavior of `To_Object` is to take\nthe ownership of the object and hence it will be released automatically.\n\n   List : Util.Beans.Objects.Object\n      := Util.Beans.Objects.To_Object (Set);"},"tagged_types":[{"id":"5a1da3e5d5cb1230","name":"Dataset","qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets.Dataset","kind":"ada_tagged_type","location":{"file":"../../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/utilada_2.8.2_30b22a59/4ad568c8d185b13a4b0f496912d263f14b692e0709f1ccf771a1531595b64c8f/src/base/beans/util-beans-objects-datasets.ads","line":62,"column":9},"code":"type Dataset is new Util.Beans.Basic.List_Bean and Iterator_Bean with private;","progenitor_types":[{"qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Basic.List_Bean","id":"ef2cc2b1b2cfd240","unit":"util-beans-basic"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets.Iterator_Bean","id":"edbb501fde8430e0","unit":"util-beans-objects-datasets-iterator_bean"}],"dispatching_declared":[{"qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets.Add_Column","id":"c5da3c559acbd31c","unit":"util-beans-objects-datasets"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets.Append","id":"67a01dd6abd54c5a","unit":"util-beans-objects-datasets"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets.Clear","id":"3e4d7a0de8eb274e","unit":"util-beans-objects-datasets"}],"dispatching_overridden":[{"qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets.Finalize","id":"5c68ef25d9b53adb","unit":"util-beans-objects-datasets"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets.First","id":"9ca0c18730576899","unit":"util-beans-objects-datasets"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets.Get_Count","id":"6e434f085c63b6b4","unit":"util-beans-objects-datasets"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets.Get_Row","id":"ce2650b96ee1ecb4","unit":"util-beans-objects-datasets"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets.Get_Value","id":"6db6b5af12eaa68e","unit":"util-beans-objects-datasets"},{"qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Datasets.Initialize","id":"f3a1cbf3024d695e","unit":"util-beans-objects-dat